Package ca.yapper.yapperapp.UMLClasses

Class Event

java.lang.Object
ca.yapper.yapperapp.UMLClasses.Event
public class Event extends Object
The Event class represents an event created by an organizer. It contains details about the event, such as name, location, date, capacity, and lists of participants in different stages (waiting, selected, cancelled, final). The class provides methods to load event details from Firestore and manage participant lists.

    • Event

      public Event(int capacity, String date_Time, String description, String facilityLocation, String facilityName, boolean isGeolocationEnabled, String name, String organizerId, String registrationDeadline, Integer waitListCapacity, ArrayList<String> cancelledList, ArrayList<String> finalList, ArrayList<String> selectedList, ArrayList<String> waitingList) throws com.google.zxing.WriterException
      Constructs a new Event with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      capacity - Maximum number of attendees.
      date_Time - The date and time of the event.
      description - Event description.
      facilityLocation - The location of the event.
      facilityName - The name of the facility.
      isGeolocationEnabled - True if geolocation is enabled for the event.
      name - The name of the event.
      registrationDeadline - Registration deadline for the event.
      waitListCapacity - Capacity of the waiting list.
      cancelledList - List of users who cancelled participation.
      finalList - Final list of participants.
      selectedList - List of selected participants.
      waitingList - Waiting list of potential participants.
      organizerId -
      Throws:
      com.google.zxing.WriterException - If there is an error generating the QR code.
